## User Preferences

### Communication Style
- **NEVER make changes beyond what was explicitly requested.** Always ask before touching files outside the scope of the task.
- **After claiming a feature is complete, verify every stated requirement was actually implemented end-to-end** -- not just the happy path, but the full round-trip (save AND restore, export AND import, write AND read, etc.). Partial implementations that only cover one direction have caused repeated frustration.
- When pre-existing test failures are encountered during regression testing, report them and ask how to proceed -- do NOT fix them without permission.
- When given a letter response (e.g., "D"), it is selecting an option from a prior multiple-choice question.
- Dislikes repetitive errors. If something has broken before, it must not break again -- add regression tests.
- Values progress tracking. Maintain `PROGRESS.md` when significant milestones are reached.

### Workflow: Git Push
- When asked to "push to github", ALWAYS run regression tests first.
- Regression test sequence: `npm run lint:all` then `npm run test:static` then `npm run type-check` then `npx ng build`.
- If any test fails, stop the push, fix the issue, re-run tests, and repeat until clean.
- Only after all tests pass, commit and push.
- After a successful push, this becomes the new regression baseline.

### Workflow: Verification After Code Changes
- ALWAYS run `npx ng build` (or check `ng serve` terminal output) after modifying component templates.
- `npm run type-check` uses `tsc` which does NOT type-check Angular inline templates -- only `ng build`/`ng serve` does.
- Static tests check structural patterns, not type correctness of template expressions.
- When adding new sub-pages or widgets with data bindings, verify property names match the backing TypeScript interfaces by running the Angular compiler.

### Workflow: Branch Management
- NEVER switch to the `main` branch automatically. Always ask the user before checking out main.
- The user prefers to stay on their current working branch (e.g., `dev`) unless explicitly told otherwise.

### Workflow: Implementation Plans
- When given a plan file, do NOT edit the plan file itself.
- Mark to-do items as in_progress as work begins.
- Work through all to-dos sequentially without stopping.
- Do not re-create to-dos that already exist.

### Workflow: Skills and Documentation
- Create skills (`.cursor/skills/`) for hard-won patterns that caused repeated failures.
- Existing skill: `dashboard-layout-lessons` covers push-squeeze, collision priority, canvas navbar, dark-mode sidenav, widget deselection, and Modus navbar native rendering fallback (Stencil/Angular 20 incompatibility).
- Existing skill: `canvas-subpage-checklist` covers the mandatory checklist for creating canvas sub-pages with tile detail expansion, list row highlighting, KPI strips, column parity, and proper navigation handlers.
- Existing skill: `view-mode-parity` enforces feature parity across desktop, canvas card, and canvas list modes. Must be followed whenever adding new data, pages, widgets, or interactions.
- Existing skill: `agentic-widgets` covers the full architecture for widget agents -- insight lines, alert badges, dynamic suggestions, cross-agent references, per-agent conversation memory, navigable links, natural language actions, and portfolio meta-agents. Must be followed when adding or modifying widget agents.
- Update `PROGRESS.md` when phases of work are completed.

## Decisions Already Made (Do Not Re-Ask)

### Architecture
- **3 main pages**: Home (`/`), Projects (`/projects`), Financials (`/financials`).
- **8 project detail pages**: Slug-based routes under `/projects/:slug`, all use shared `ProjectDashboardComponent`.
- **Shared layout engine**: `DashboardLayoutEngine` service manages drag, resize, push-squeeze, and collision for all dashboard pages.
- **Dashboard shell**: `DashboardShellComponent` provides navbar, sidenav, AI panel, and document-level event handling for all pages.
- **Canvas mode**: Activates at viewport >= 1920px with fixed navbar (1280px centered), spacebar panning, and overlap resolution.
- **Widget persistence**: sessionStorage per-page/per-project. Not server-side yet.
- **Canvas zoom**: Anchors to viewport center (not cursor). Triggers: Shift+scroll, Ctrl+scroll, Cmd+scroll. Uses `Math.abs` comparison of both delta axes to handle macOS axis swapping.
- **Layout storage keys**: desktop `project-${id}-v4`, canvas `canvas-layout:project-${id}:v6`.

### Design System
- **9-color system only**: background, foreground, card, muted, secondary, primary, success, warning, destructive.
- **No emojis anywhere**: Use Modus icons instead.
- **Div-only HTML**: No semantic elements (h1, p, section, header, etc.).
- **Custom opacity utilities**: `-80`, `-60`, `-40`, `-20` suffix, not Tailwind `/80` syntax.
- **Custom border utilities**: `border-default`, `border-primary`, etc.
- **Modus icons with underscores**: `save_disk`, `arrow_left`, `check_circle`.
- **Modus Typography enforced**: All text sizing/weight on div/span must use `<modus-typography>`. `text-2xs` mapped to `size="xs" className="text-2xs"`; `font-medium` mapped to `weight="semibold"`. Static test `tests/static/typography-enforcement.spec.ts` enforces. Exceptions: `innerHTML` rendered HTML (e.g., AI assistant).

### Layout Engine Behavior
- **Push-squeeze on resize**: Push all neighbors first (maintaining widths), then squeeze from far end inward to 4-column minimum, then relocate outermost if still overflowing.
- **Collision priority**: Widgets actively placed by push-squeeze get priority in vertical collision resolution. Relocated widgets yield.
- **Push-down only collision**: Both `resolveCollisions` and `compactAll` initialize widget `y` from `tops[id]`, never from `0`. Widgets can only be pushed down by overlaps -- they never jump upward over intervening widgets. Only explicit user drag can move a widget across others.
- **Horizontal resize dead zone**: For `dir='both'`, horizontal resize pipeline (`applyResizePushSqueeze`, `syncColsFromPixelPositions`) only activates when horizontal mouse delta exceeds half a column step. Prevents twitchy neighbor widgets during vertical-only resize.
- **Click outside deselects**: Clicking anywhere not inside `[data-widget-id]` clears widget selection.

### Canvas Navbar
- **overflow: visible** on `.canvas-navbar`. NEVER set to hidden (clips dropdowns). This has regressed before.
- **border-radius** applied to inner `.canvas-navbar modus-wc-navbar .modus-wc-navbar` for visual rounding.

### Dark Mode Side Nav
- `modus-classic-dark`: side nav uses `var(--modus-wc-color-gray-10)` to match navbar.
- `modus-modern-dark`: side nav uses `var(--modus-wc-color-trimble-gray)` to match navbar.
- Other themes: default `var(--background)` is correct.

