## Known Fragile Areas

These areas have broken multiple times. Extra care required:

| Area | Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------|------------|
| Hamburger/sidenav | Modus navbar has NO shadow DOM (scoped encapsulation); `shadowRoot` is always null; `mainMenuOpenChange` event bubbles and can double-fire | Search light DOM with `navbarWc.querySelector()`, not `shadowRoot.querySelector()`. Fallback must be idempotent `set(open)`, not toggle. See skill section 16 |
| Canvas navbar overflow | Setting `overflow: hidden` clips dropdowns | Static test asserts `overflow: visible`; border-radius on inner element |
| Push-squeeze ordering | Wrong cascade order causes incorrect widget relocation | Unit tests cover right-edge and left-edge squeeze ordering |
| Collision after resize | Active vs relocated widget priority | `_pushSqueezeActive` set tracks active widgets; unit tests cover |
| Widget deselection | Missing `data-widget-id` attribute breaks click-outside | All widget containers must have `[attr.data-widget-id]` |
| Canvas BFS cascade direction | Cascade pusher uses own center for direction, bouncing widgets back toward mover | Direction always references mover center; 16 unit tests in `canvas-push.spec.ts` |
| Canvas detail double rAF | Single rAF reads stale dimensions, pushes incorrectly | Always use double `requestAnimationFrame` before push; see skill section 7 |
| Canvas zoom macOS axis swap | macOS swaps deltaY→deltaX when Shift held; deltaY is 0, zoom direction resolves wrong | Use `Math.abs` comparison of both axes; pick whichever is larger |
| Navbar native rendering (Stencil/Angular 20) | `modus-wc-toolbar` fails to render in dev mode; developers add/remove custom elements creating duplicates in prod or missing elements in dev. Has broken 5+ times. | Runtime detection via `navbarNativeRendered` signal + conditional fallback. All 4 navbar instances must stay in sync. See skill section 23 |
| Shell ng-content in conditional branches | Placing `<ng-content />` inside `@if`/`@else` branches silently destroys projected content. Broke ALL dashboard pages in canvas mode for 2 days (PR #56, Apr 3-5). | Shell must have **exactly 1** `<ng-content />` outside ALL conditional blocks. Static test enforces count and nesting. See skill section 29 |
| Resize twitchiness (`dir='both'`) | Horizontal resize pipeline runs on every frame during vertical-only resize, causing pixel-column round-trip jitter that twitches neighbors | `_hResizeActive` gate: horizontal pipeline only activates after horizontal mouse delta exceeds half a column step. See skill section 32 |
| Widget jumping (collision compaction) | `resolveCollisions` and `compactAll` starting at `y=0` causes distant widgets to teleport upward over intervening widgets | Always start at `tops[id]`; widgets can only move down. See skill section 33 |
| Vercel CDN stale HTML | CDN caches `index.html` for 26+ hours, serving old JS bundles missing new routes | `Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate` on HTML responses in `vercel.json` |
| Vercel Angular build cache | `.angular/cache` persists stale route definitions across deploys | `rm -rf .angular/cache` before `npm run build` in `vercel.json` |
| Zone.js context loss (auth callback) | trimble-id library uses axios/CommonJS which exits Zone.js context; post-auth `navigateByUrl` silently fails | Wrap in `NgZone.run()`; add `window.location.replace` hard-redirect fallback |
| Layout seed sharing across personas | Shared "default" seeds meant editing one persona broke others; `exportLayoutSeed()` run with wrong persona overwrote shared file (broke Frank/Bert canvas mode Apr 12-13) | Eliminated ALL shared seeds. 5 personas x 4 pages = 20 independent seed files. 288 static tests in `layout-seeds.spec.ts` enforce file existence, widget lists, no-contamination, geometry, per-persona routing, and export map. See skill section 37 |

